1> 1.  When pulling a mob from the center of the zone, try guiding it to the nearest wall, and than along the wall back to your group to pick up less or no adds.<br>
<br>
2.  Running start.  using a ranged attack or spell allows for a head start to keep from getting hit.  This is especially good for rangers with jolt, as they can jolt the mob when the target reaches the group to nullify all agro from the pull<br>
<br>
3.  Undead Mobs in Living zones.  Using camouflage to bypass living mobs, approach an Undead mob until it agros on you, keep your distance and prevent it from hitting you to keep camoflage up and you'll bring it back without agroing any living mobs<br>
<br>
4.  Long pulls, take your time, keep the mob isolated and concentrated on you<br>
<br>
5.  Snare pulling.  Snare should only be used to pull when the group may need some time to prepare for the mob, or if they are fighting another mob at the moment.  This also allows you to run back and join your group due to snares significant agro.<br>
